Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette(?) bowl; glaze fired orange-red; interior glazed; exterior: top of lip glazed; some verticals preserved in lip zone; inscription in reserved zone.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.855)
